OpenOffice 1.0.3.1 for Linux

Download from http://www.openoffice.org/dev_docs/source/1.0.3/#linux
("BinaryCode" site was very slow, "Indiana U" site was fine.)

Installation instructions:
http://www.openoffice.org/dev_docs/instructions.html

## First, system-wide installation
mkdir ~mernst/tmp/oo-install
mv OOo_1.0.3.1_LinuxIntel_install.tar.gz ~mernst/tmp/oo-install
cd ~mernst/tmp/oo-install
tar -zxf OOo_1.0.3.1_LinuxIntel_install.tar.gz
cd install
sudo ./setup -net
#  Install into /usr/local/OpenOffice.org1.0.3
sudo mv /usr/local/bin/soffice /usr/local/bin/soffice-1.0.2
sudo ln -s /usr/local/OpenOffice.org1.0.3/program/soffice /usr/local/bin/soffice

## Now, per-user installation.
## Note I am not root while executing the following.
# The following commands may be necessary in the midst of the "setup" command.
sudo chown -R mernst ~/.kde2
sudo chgrp -R mernst ~/.kde2
sudo chown mernst ~/.gnome/apps/OpenOffice.org\ 1.0.3
sudo chgrp mernst ~/.gnome/apps/OpenOffice.org\ 1.0.3
# On older machines, use ".kde" instead of ".kde2" here.
(cd ~/.kde2/share; mkdir -p icons/locolor/16x16/apps icons/locolor/32x32/apps icons/hicolor/32x32/apps icons/hicolor/48x48/apps)
# Actual installation:  (choose "workstation installation"?)

/usr/local/OpenOffice.org1.0.3/setup &
# Choose ~/.OpenOffice.org1.0.3/

===========================================================================

OpenOffice 1.0.2 for Linux

Download from http://www.openoffice.org/dev_docs/source/1.0.2/index.html#linux
(This took 15+ minutes on 5/31/2002.)

Installation instructions:
http://www.openoffice.org/dev_docs/instructions.html

## First, system-wide installation
mkdir ~mernst/tmp/oo-install
mv OOo_1.0.2_LinuxIntel_install.tar.gz ~mernst/tmp/oo-install
cd ~mernst/tmp/oo-install
tar -zxf OOo_1.0.2_LinuxIntel_install.tar.gz
cd install
sudo ./setup -net
#  Install into /usr/local/OpenOffice.org1.0.2
sudo mv /usr/local/bin/soffice /usr/local/bin/soffice-old
sudo ln -s /usr/local/OpenOffice.org1.0.2/program/soffice /usr/local/bin/soffice

## Now, per-user installation.
## Note I am not root while executing the following.
# The following commands may be necessary in the midst of the "setup" command.
sudo chown -R mernst ~/.kde2
sudo chgrp -R mernst ~/.kde2
sudo chown mernst ~/.gnome/apps/OpenOffice.org\ 1.0.2
sudo chgrp mernst ~/.gnome/apps/OpenOffice.org\ 1.0.2
# On older machines, use ".kde" instead of ".kde2" here.
(cd ~/.kde2/share; mkdir -p icons/locolor/16x16/apps icons/locolor/32x32/apps icons/hicolor/32x32/apps icons/hicolor/48x48/apps)
# Actual installation:
/usr/local/OpenOffice.org1.0.2/setup &
cd /usr/local/OpenOffice.org1.0.2
./setup &
# Choose ~/.OpenOffice.org1.0.2/

